In JIRA v4.4.4 the workflow viewer represents every status and every transition in the workflow as if they were equivalent. There is nothing to show that a transition from the current status is not currently possible.  It would help if the viewer clearly indicated the difference between valid and invalid transitions.  Perhaps by use of colour, or a dashed line instead of solid?

Simple example:  Create a condition for the Resolve Issue Transition "All sub-tasks must have one of the following statuses to allow parent issue transitions: Resolved or Closed.",  Users have problems with this in that the Resolve or Close actions are sometimes available and sometimes not (dependent on the sub-tasks).  When the actions are not available and they click on "View Workflow" it tells them contradictory information...  it seems to indicate that they should be able to Resolve/Close.  This causes confusion and leads to support calls.

